\\\"300\\\" /></a>\\\" width=\\\"\\\" height=\\\"\\\" /&gt;\\\"&gt;[/image_frame]\r\nFormer B&amp;D Thunder player, Legend Robertin commited to join the Division 1 Clemson Tigers to continue his basketball dream. The 7 footer from London had offers from other division 1 powerhouse schools such as Memphis, Indiana, Oklahoma St, Alabama and others but elected to join Clemson who has a rich tradition of former stars including Horace Grant, Elden Campbell and Rick Barnes.</div>\r\n<div>Legend proclaimed \\\"I went from shooting 50 lay ups each side on Saturday morning at Dagenham Park to playing in the ACC, I\\\'ve come a long way and it has been an amazing journey so far!\\\"</div>\r\n<div>Beginning his new adventure in the fall as a junior, all the Thunder family wish Legend all the best for the upcoming season! We will continue to keep you posted of Legends progress as the season develops! #thunderfamily\r\n\r\n\r\n<div><strong>Clemson Tigers Basketball Website: <a href=\\\"http://www.clemsontigers.com/SportSelect.dbml?SPID=103715\\\">http://www.clemsontigers.com/SportSelect.dbml?SPID=103715</a></strong></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n[otw_shortcode_divider margin_top_bottom=\\\"30\\\" text_position=\\\"otw-text-left\\\"][/otw_shortcode_divider]\r\n<div style=\\\"width: 40%; padding: 0 5pt 0 0; float: left;\\\">[fancy_header]New B&amp;D Wheelchair Basketball[/fancy_header]\r\n[image_frame style=\\\"framed\\\" align=\\\"left\\\" height=\\\"150\\\" width=\\\"150\\\"]<a href=\\\"http://www.thunderbasketball.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Inclusive-Wheelchair-Basketball-Sessions-BD-flyer3-1.jpg\\\"><img class=\\\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-867\\\" alt=\\\"WCBasketball \\\" src=\\\"http://www.thunderbasketball.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Inclusive-Wheelchair-Basketball-Sessions-BD-flyer3-1-213x300.jpg\\\" width=\\\"213\\\" height=\\\"300\\\" /></a>\\\" width=\\\"\\\" height=\\\"\\\" /&gt;\\\"&gt;[/image_frame]Barking &amp; Dagenham Sports Development Team, in partnership with Access Sport Ignite Programme, Motivate East and Thunder Basketball Club have recently launched a new inclusive wheelchair basketball session at Dagenham Park School.\r\nFunded by Access Sport Ignite Programme, the launch event held on October 4th saw 38 young people aged between 11 and 25 years, take part in a three hour session that was delivered by experienced coaches from Thunder Basketball Club and volunteers from Barking and Dagenham Community Volunteer Team â€¦Â <strong><span style=\\\"color: #ff0000;\\\"><em><a href=\\\"http://www.thunderbasketball.co.uk/bd-wheelchair-basketball-2/\\\" title=\\\"B&D Wheelchair Basketball\\\">Read More</a></em></span></strong></div>\r\n<div style=\\\"width: 40%; padding: 0 3pt 0 0; float: right;\\\">[fancy_header]B&D 3 on 3 U16 CHAMPIONSHIP Tournament[/fancy_header]\r\n[image_frame style=\\\"framed\\\" align=\\\"left\\\" height=\\\"150\\\" width=\\\"150\\\"]<a href=\\\"http://www.thunderbasketball.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/3on31.jpg\\\"><img class=\\\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-896\\\" alt=\\\"3on31\\\" src=\\\"http://www.thunderbasketball.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/3on31-300x225.jpg\\\" width=\\\"300\\\" height=\\\"225\\\" /></a>\\\" width=\\\"\\\" height=\\\"\\\" /&gt;\\\"&gt;[/image_frame]B&amp;D 3 on 3 U16 Championship Tournament is coming up soon! Experienced or inexperienced you can still take part. Don\\\'t miss your chance to participate!There are many ways to get involved, you can participate as a player or volunteer. Whatever your interest we would love for you to be part. \r\n\r\n<strong>MORE INFO COMING SOON</strong></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=\\\"width: 40%; padding: 0 5pt 0 0; float: right;\\\"><strong></strong></div>\";s:16:\"mainpage_content\";s:0:\"\";s:22:\"homepage_footer_teaser\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"image_resize_type\";s:8:\"timthumb\";s:25:\"one_column_portfolio_full\";a:2:{s:1:\"w\";s:3:\"882\";s:1:\"h\";s:3:\"547\";}s: