spiring players in the region. Established in 2008 by Managing Director, Marlan Henry and a regional school sports partnership, Henry drove a community after-school program to encourage basketball. A subsequent link to the Barking &amp; Dagenham Primary School was established which founded the \"Gifted &amp; Talented\" sessions that offered various sporting activities.Â The sessions were well received and an under-12 team was formed, which took part in local tournaments and the London Youth Games.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>In 2011, Marlan Henry acquired a former teammate from the London Leopards, RÃ¡vidson Teixeira to become a part of the Thunder coaching staff. With the Thunderâ€™s national league squad playing their second season in the EBL U15â€™s, coach Ravidson assisted Henry throughout the season, contributing to the clubâ€™s growth. Since established, the club now runs a total of three teams in the national league (u14, u16 and u18â€™s boys) as well as u12â€™s mixed and u16 girls in the local league.\r\nThe club has forged outstanding relationships within the community and continue to grow and welcome players of all standards to join and enjoy the sport. Several key players left to further their basketball development overseas.\r\n\r\n</div>','About Us','','inherit','open','open','','20-revision-v1','','','2014-12-16 20:32:50','2014-12-16 20:32:50','',20,'http://www.thunderbasketball.co.uk/20-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1068,1,'2014-12-16 20:29:24','2014-12-16 20:29:24','B&amp;D Thunder Basketball Club is an English club based in borough Barking and Dagenham, playing in the England Basketball League (EBL). The club was developed with the purpose of providing opportunities for youth to develop the skills and fundamentals of the sport, as well as offer high quality organized basketball. The club runs several programs both male and female ranging from the ages of 8 to 18 as well as the boroughs youth team.\r\n\r\nIn 2008, Thunder managing director &amp; founder Marlan Henry together with B&amp;D School Sports Partnership drove a community after-school programme to encourage young people to take part in basketball. A link was furthermore formed with Barking and Dagenham Primary School to form a â€œGifted and Talentedâ€ session, which offered young people with sporting abilities an opportunity to participate in new activities. The sessions were well received and an under-12 team was formed, which took part in local tournaments and London Youth Games.\r\n\r\nIn 2011, Marlan Henry acquired a former teammate from the London Leopards, RÃ¡vidson Teixeira to become a part of the Thunder coaching staff. With the Thunderâ€™s national league squad playing their second season in the EBL U15â€™s, coach Ravidson assisted Henry throughout the season, contributing to the clubâ€™s growth. Since established, the club now runs a total of three teams in the national league (u14, u16 and u18â€™s boys) as well as u12â€™s mixed and u16 girls in the local league.\r\n\r\nBarking and Dagenham Thunder have joined together with TEAM Foundation, which was established in February 2012, the TEAM (Together Everybody Achieves More) foundation was formed with a focus to develop and enhance sporting opportunities to young people in the London region. Our goals are to ensure young people are placed at the centre of everything we aspire to do regardless of background, religious beliefs, culture and circumstances. This enables Thunder to have the support from the organisation and to have the experience and knowledge from TEAM Foundation staff.\r\n\r\nTEAM Foundation focuses on making a difference in the youth community with the emphasis to promote sports and healthy team competition. Team foundation for example established a basketball clinic offering free coaching and basketball lessons for 11-19 year olds in the Barking and Dagenham area. In addition to sports, team foundation offers mentoring and guidance to the youth and underprivileged to assist in tackling the key issues that young people face in todayâ€™s society. Team foundation is committed to challenging inequality and to maximising opportunities and choices, particularly for young people who may be less fortunate educationally, socially and economically, with the Upcoming Basketball clinics at Sydney Russell School hoping to be a continued success from the summer.','About Us','','inherit','open','open','','20-revision-v1','','','2014-12-16 20:29:24','2014-12-16 20:29:24','',20,'http://www.thunderbasketball.co.uk/20-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(21,1,'2012-10-25 20:12:34','2012-10-25 20:12:34','','About Us','','inherit','open','open','','20-revision-v1','','','2012-10-25 20:12:34','2012-10-25 20:12:34','',20,'http://www.thunderbasketball.co.uk/blog/20-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(22,1,'2012-10-25 20:12:47','2012-10-25 20:12:47','This is an example page. It\'s different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:\r\n\r\n<blockquote>Hi there! I\'m a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my blog. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like pi&#241;a coladas. (And gettin\' caught in the rain.)</blockquote>\r\n\r\n...or something like this:\r\n\r\n<blockquote>The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickies to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.</blockquote>\r\n\r\nAs a new WordPress user, you should go to <a href=\"http://www.thunderbasketball.co.uk/blog/wp-admin/\">your dashboard</a> to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!','About Us','','inherit','open','open','','20-revision-v1','','','2012-10-25 20:12:47','2012-10-25 20:12:47','',20,'http://www.thunderb