.thunderbasketball.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/DSC_1155.jpg\"><img src=\"http://www.thunderbasketball.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/DSC_1155-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"DSC_1155\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-291\" /></a>[/image_frame]B&D Thunder\'s Robinson Idehen\'s versilitiy combined with height and speed on the court offers the club an abundance of options both offensively and defensively. Born in Spain with a Nigerian background, Robinson moved to England at the age of 12 and has been part of the Thunder programme for three years now. Through an agreement with the Thunder, Robinson now attends Barking Abbey Academy, one of the premier basketball academies in Europe. Standing 6\'7, Robinson had a fantastic 2012 and quickly emerged as only of the standout players in the UK - so much so that he was selected to join up with the Spanish U16 team having been scouted by Luis Guil who contacted the Spanish Federation. Guil himself was a former Spanish international and applied his trade in Europe in the ACB and is currently Barking Abbeys coach. \r\n\r\nThunder coach Marlan Henry accompanied Robinson on his trip to Spain to participate in the annual Iscar tournament which lasted over 7 days.\r\nAlthough slightly nervous as it was his first time travelling without his family, Robinson leaned on the support of coach Henry and stated \"having this opportunity was a great experience for me as a basketball player, I\'ve learnt a lot in those 7 days. Sometime it did feel like information overload but I made the adjustment\"\r\n\r\n[image_frame style=\"framed\" align=\"right\" height=\"150\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"http://www.thunderbasketball.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/DSC_2353.jpg\"><img src=\"http://www.thunderbasketball.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/DSC_2353-300x188.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"DSC_2353\" width=\"300\" height=\"188\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-290\" /></a>[/image_frame]