]\r\n<h4>Jackie Reed</h4>\r\n<h6>Welfare Officer</h6>\r\nResponsible for the safeguard of every child who comes in contact with Thunder. Jackie is a parent who is consistently present in practices and games. Always happy to see a new face around.\r\n\r\nHobbies: \r\n[/three_fourth_last]\r\n\r\n[divider_padding]\r\n\r\n[one_fourth]\r\n[image_frame style=\"framed_shadow\"]http://themes.mysitemyway.com/images/content/about_us.png[/image_frame]\r\n[/one_fourth]\r\n\r\n[three_fourth_last]\r\n<h4>Shane Cabak</h4>\r\n<h6>Marketing</h6>\r\nLike many parents Ms Shane is a parent on the sideline watching her kid go up and down chasing the ball, her energy and vision to help the club is phenomenal, always looking to get the word out in the community and get more kids involved with the program.\r\n\r\nHobbies: \r\n[/three_fourth_last]\r\n\r\n[divider_padding]\r\n\r\n[one_fourth]\r\n[image_frame style=\"framed_shadow\"]http://themes.mysitemyway.com/images/content/about_us.png[/image_frame]\r\n[/one_fourth]\r\n\r\n[three_fourth_last]\r\n<h4>Julie Walsh</h4>\r\n<h6>Fundraiser</h6>\r\nJulie is a parent and although she has only been with us since last year, her commitment to help the club has been great. Welcome onboard!\r\n\r\nHobbies: \r\n[/three_fourth_last]\r\n\r\n[divider_padding]\r\n\r\n[one_fourth]\r\n[image_frame style=\"framed_shadow\"]<a href=\"http://www.thunderbasketball.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/DSC_0925.jpg\"><img src=\"http://www.thunderbasketball.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/DSC_0925-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"DSC_0925\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-278\" /></a>[/image_frame]\r\n[/one_fourth]\r\n\r\n[three_fourth_last]\r\n<h4>Rikki Broadmore</h4>\r\n<h6>U18 Head Coach</h6>\r\nCoach Broadmore, a new addition to the Thunder coaching staff is a former basketball player who is involved with the England Basketball. Rikki has assisted the U16 girls England squad who won the promotion last year from Division B to Division A European Championship. He is also the lead coach for the U14 Barking Abbey School team which successfully won back to back National Schools Titles in 2010 and 2011.\r\n\r\nHobbies: \r\n[/three_fourth_last]\r\n\r\n[divider_padding]\r\n\r\n[one_fourth]\r\n[image_frame style=\"framed_shadow\"]http://themes.mysitemyway.com/images/content/about_us.png[/image_frame]\r\n[/one_fourth]\r\n\r\n[three_fourth_last]\r\n<h4>Cheraine Ncube</h4>\r\n<h6>U16 Girls Head Coach</h6>\r\nThe Thunder is proud to have its first girlâ€™s basketball team and its newest coaching member Cheraine Ncube. Coach Cheraine who has played the game in the past is new to the coaching life style, but her energy and knowledge of the game makes up for her experience behind the play book.\r\n\r\nHobbies: Basketball, Reading, Music, Sending time with friends and family\r\n[/three_fourth_last]\r\n\r\n[divider_padding]\r\n\r\n[one_fourth]\r\n[image_frame style=\"framed_shadow\"]<a href=\"http://www.thunderbasketball.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/DSC_27542.jpg\"><img src=\"http://www.thunderbasketball.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/DSC_27542.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"DSC_2754\" width=\"150\" height=\"225\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-363\" /></a>[/image_frame]\r\n[/one_fourth]\r\n\r\n[three_fourth_last]\r\n<h4>Maiklas Vasiliauskas</h4>\r\n<h6>U12 Head Coach</h6>\r\nMike started has a volunteer helping coaches with the early sessions before his team practice. His dedication and role has seen him excel within the club, not only Mike plays for our U18 but he is also a role model for our younger kids. He is respected and treated like any member of coaching staff.\r\n\r\nHobbies: Music, Basketball\r\n[/three_fourth_last]\r\n\r\n[divider_padding]','Our Staff','','inherit','open','open','','65-revision-v1','','','2013-01-16 21:20:05','2013-01-16 21:20:05','',65,'http://www.thunderbasketball.co.uk/65-revision-44/',0,'revision','',0),(640,1,'2014-04-01 09:25:46','2014-04-01 09:25:4