 Every morning we worked out at 6am before school doing sprints, weights and agility training then did shooting drills in the evenings. Iâ€™m 6â€™8 so naturally everyone thinks I should be a big man in the post, but we work a lot on my guard skills and watched film.\r\n\r\n<strong>Tell us about your battles with Coach Marlan Henry?</strong>\r\nMan!! It gets really competitive! Coach Marlan hates losing more than winning so that says a lot. We play one on one all the time, Iâ€™ve never won YET! I will one day, its definately one of my top goals!\r\n\r\n<strong>December 2012 was a huge turning point you as a young basketball player.</strong>\r\nYes it was! I had the chance to go to the Spanish National Team training camp and tournament in Iscar, Spain.\r\nI was excited and nervous at the same time! My parents couldnâ€™t take me because they both had work and I was too young to travel on my own, so my Thunder coach (Marlan Henry) went on the trip with. We landed in Madrid, picked up by the rest of the team and drove a couple of hours to Iscar.\r\nThe biggest adjustment for me was learning the system in the short 10 days. Iâ€™ve never been in a situation like this so I didnâ€™t really know what to expect. There was like 15 coaches at camp, doctor, physio. Everything was so well organized, I didnâ€™t know what to expect but this was on another level.\r\n\r\nCoach Marlan didnâ€™t find it that easy, he hates the cold and doesnâ€™t speak any Spanish at all! I was a translator most of the time! As time went on he picked up a few words and now he thinks heâ€™s Spanish!\r\n\r\n<strong>Do you feel experience has opened a lot of opportunities for you?</strong>\r\nYes it has! Iâ€™ve now moved back to Spain, this time itâ€™s just me. My family still live in London and Iâ€™m in Majadahonda. I attend El BonsoÃ±io School and play my club basketball for Baloncesto Majadahonda.\r\nOver the summer I had to make adecision, stay in London or move to Spain. It wasnâ€™t easy, Iâ€™m only 15 and it was a big step for me. Talking to my family and coaches helped, they where very supportive in my decision and it was the right one.\r\n\r\n<strong>Apart from basketball what else do you do?</strong>\r\nLast year I really got into high jump, I thought Iâ€™d give it a try and represented my school in the borough athletics competition. Ended up breaking the borough record at 1.85 meters.\r\nMusic is also a big part of my life and was introduced to it by my dad, he plays the guitar and drums at church. I started playing at 4 years old. My dad and I canâ€™t read music so we do everything from ear. I now play the guitar, drums, and piano. Hopefully Iâ€™ll learn how to read music.\r\n\r\n<strong>Who is your favorite player?</strong>\r\nKevin Durant is a player I really look up to. His combination of versatility, size and skills is something I aspire my game to reach towards.\r\n\r\n<strong>What are you goals for the future?</strong>\r\nNext year I want to be on the Spanish U18 National Team and also have the opportunity to play at the College level in the US. It will offer me an excellent platform for education, to grow and also develop my basketball skills to the next level. Im excited for the future.\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>[/two_third]</div>\r\n[one_fourth_last]\r\n\r\n[colored_box title=\"<strong>NEXT HOME GAME</strong>\"]<strong>Saturday 16th Nov 2013</strong>\r\n\r\nU13 vs Newham Youngbloods Aces, 12.15pm Tip off!\r\n\r\nU15 vs Newham Youngbloods Dynamos, 2pm Tip off!\r\n\r\nU18 Con vs Brixton Topcats, 4pm Tip off!\r\n\r\nU18 Prem vs Bristol Academy Flyers, 6pm Tip off!\r\n\r\n[twitter-feed username=\"bdtbasketball\" id=\"123456789\"]\r\n\r\n<strong>Venue</strong>\r\n\r\nBarking Abbey School Leisure Centre, Woodbridge Road, Barking IG11 9ET.[/colored_box]\r\n\r\n[colored_box title=\"<strong>Robinson Idehen - Spain</strong>\"]<strong>[youtube url=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iKS6FYjysPM\" width=\"600\"\r\nheight=\"300\" autohide=\"0\" autoplay=\"0\" controls=\"1\" disablekb=\"1\" fs=\"1\"\r\nhd=\"1\" loop=\"1\" rel=\"0\" showsearch=\"0\" showinfo=\"0\"][/colored_box]</strong>\r\n\r\n[colored_box variation=\"white\" title=\"<strong>Like us on Facebook</strong>\"]<iframe style=\"border: none; overflow: hidden; width: 200px; height: 258px;\" src=\"//www.facebook.com/plugins/likebox.php?href=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2Fbdthunderbasketball&amp;width=200&amp;height=258&amp;colorscheme=light&amp;show_faces=true&amp;header=false&amp;stream=false&amp;show_border=false\" height=\"240\" width=\"320\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\"></iframe>[/colored_box]\r\n\r\n[colored_box variation=\"white\" title=\"<strong>Like us on Twitter</strong>\"]<a class=\"twitter-timeline\" href=\"https://twitter.com/BDTBasketball\" data-widget-id=\"402703896830672896\">Tweets by @BDTBasketball</a>\r\n<script type=\"text/javascript\">// <![CDATA[\r\n!function(d,s,id){var js,fjs=d.getElementsByTagName(s)[0],p=/^http:/.test(d.location)?\'http\':\'https\';if(!d.getElementById(id)){js=d.createElement(s);js.id=id;js.src=p+\"://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\";fjs.parentNode.insertBefore(js,fjs);}}(document,\"script\",\"twitter-wjs\");\r\n// ]]></script>\r\n\r\n[/colored_box]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[/one_fourth_last]','TEST PAGE','','inherit','open','open','','147-revision-v1','','','2014-04-02 06:46:17','2014-04-02 06:46:17','',147,'http://www.thunderbasketball.co.uk/147-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1718,1,'2016-06-14 11:34:28','2016-06-14 11:34:28','<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"http://www.thunderbasketball.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/BADThunderTryoutArtwork1.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-1712\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1612 size-medium\" src=\"http://www.thunderbasketball.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/BADThunderTryoutArtwork1-300x150.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"150\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">**BAD Thunder National League Open Tryouts**</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Satur