 it that easy, he hates the cold and doesnâ€™t speak any Spanish at all! I was a translator most of the time! As time went on he picked up a few words and now he thinks heâ€™s Spanish!\r\n\r\n<strong>Do you feel experience has opened a lot of opportunities for you?</strong>\r\nYes it has! Iâ€™ve now moved back to Spain, this time itâ€™s just me. My family still live in London and Iâ€™m in Majadahonda. I attend El BonsoÃ±io School and play my club basketball for Baloncesto Majadahonda.\r\nOver the summer I had to make adecision, stay in London or move to Spain. It wasnâ€™t easy, Iâ€™m only 15 and it was a big step for me. Talking to my family and coaches helped, they where very supportive in my decision and it was the right one.\r\n\r\n<strong>Apart from basketball what else do you do?</strong>\r\nLast year I really got into high jump, I thought Iâ€™d give it a try and represented my school in the borough athletics competition. Ended up breaking the borough record at 1.85 meters.\r\nMusic is also a big part of my life and was introduced to it by my dad, he plays the guitar and drums at church. I started playing at 4 years old. My dad and I canâ€™t read music so we do everything from ear. I now play the guitar, drums, and piano. Hopefully Iâ€™ll learn how to read music.\r\n\r\n<strong>Who is your favorite player?</strong>\r\nKevin Durant is a player I really look up to. His combination of versatility, size and skills is something I aspire my game to reach towards.\r\n\r\n<strong>What are you goals for the future?</strong>\r\nNext year I want to be on the Spanish U18 National Team and also have the opportunity to play at the College level in the US. It will offer me an excellent platform for education, to grow and also develop my basketball skills to the next level. Im excited for the future.\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>[/two_third]</div>\r\n[one_fourth_last]\r\n\r\n[colored_box title=\"<strong>NEXT HOME GAME</strong>\"]<strong>Saturday 16th Nov 2013</strong>\r\n\r\nU13 vs 