th team.\r\n\r\nIn 2008, Thunder managing director & founder Marlan Henry together with B&D School Sports Partnership drove a community after-school programme to encourage young people to take part in basketball. A link was furthermore formed with Barking and Dagenham Primary School to form a â€œGifted and Talentedâ€ session, which offered young people with sporting abilities an opportunity to participate in new activities. The sessions were well received and an under-12 team was formed, which took part in local tournaments and London Youth Games.\r\n\r\nIn 2011, Marlan Henry acquired a former teammate from the London Leopards, RÃ¡vidson Teixeira to become a part of the Thunder coaching staff. With the Thunderâ€™s national league squad playing their second season in the EBL U15â€™s, coach Ravidson assisted Henry throughout the season, contributing to the clubâ€™s growth. Since established, the club now runs a total of three teams in the national league (u14, u16 and u18â€™s boys) as well as u12â€™s mixed and u16 girls in the local league.\r\n\r\nBarking and Dagenham Thunder have joined together with TEAM Foundation, which was established in February 2012, the TEAM (Together Everybody Achieves More) foundation was formed with a focus to develop and enhance sporting opportunities to young people in the London region. Our goals are to ensure young people are placed at the centre of everything we aspire to do regardless of background, religious beliefs, culture and circumstances.  This enables Thunder to have the support from the organisation and to have the experience and knowledge from TEAM Foundation staff. \r\n\r\nTEAM Foundation focuses on making a difference in the youth community with the emphasis to promote sports and healthy team competition. Team foundation for example established a basketball clinic offering free coaching and basketball lessons for 11-19 year olds in the Barking and Dagenham area. In addition to sports, team foundation offers mentoring and g