/',0,'revision','',0),(887,1,'2014-11-09 15:29:04','2014-11-09 15:29:04','[fancy_header]Thunders Legend joins NCAA Division 1 side, Clemson Tigers[/fancy_header]\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>\r\n[image_frame style=\"framed\" align=\"left\" height=\"\" width=\"\"]<a href=\"&lt;a href=\"><img alt=\"Untitled\" src=\"http://www.thunderbasketball.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/Untitled1-300x224.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"224\" /></a>\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /&gt;\"&gt;[/image_frame]\r\n\r\nFormer (tag) B&amp;D Thunder player, (tag) Legend Robertin commited to join the Divison 1(tag) Clemson Tigers to continue his basketball dream. The 7 footer from London had offers from other division 1 powerhouse schools such as Memphis, Indiana, Oklahoma St, Alabama and others but elected to join Clemson who has a rich tradition of former stars including (tag) Horace Grant, Elden Campbell and Rick Barnes.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div>Legend proclaimed \"I went from shooting 50 lay ups each side on Saturday morning at Dagenham Park to playing in the ACC, I\'ve come a long way and it has been an amazing journey so far!\"</div>\r\n<div>Beginning his new adventure in the fall as a junior, all the Thunder family wish Legend all the best for the upcoming season! We will continue to keep you posted of Legends progress as the season develops! #thunderfamily</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>Clemson Tigers Basketball Website: <a href=\"http://www.clemsontigers.com/SportSelect.dbml?SPID=103715\">http://www.clemsontigers.com/SportSelect.dbml?SPID=103715</a></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n[otw_shortcode_divider margin_top_bottom=\"30\" text_position=\"otw-text-left\"][/otw_shortcode_divider]\r\n<div style=\"width: 40%; padding: 0 5pt 0 0; float: left;\">[fancy_header]New B&amp;D Wheelchair Basketball[/fancy_header]\r\n[image_frame style=\"framed\" align=\"left\" height=\"150\" width=\"150\"]<img alt=\"536256_587061181395678_2599361266593340468_n\" src=\"http://www.thunderbasketball.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/536256_587061181395678_2599361266593340468_n-e1413958420393-150x150.jpg\" width=\"54\" height=\"54\" />\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /&gt;\"&gt;[/image_frame]\r\n\r\nBarking &amp; Dagenham Sports Development Team, in partnership with Access Sport Ignite Programme, Motivate East and Thunder Basketball Club have recently launched a new inclusive wheelchair basketball session at Dagenham Park School.\r\nFunded by Access Sport Ignite Programme, the launch event held on October 4th saw 38 young people aged between 11 and 25 years, take part in a three hour session that was delivered by experienced coaches from Thunder Basketball Club and volunteers from Barking and Dagenham Community Volunteer Team ...<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><em>Read More</em></span> using sports wheelchairs kindly on loan from Motivate East.\r\nThe event was to launch weekly inclusive wheelchair basketball sessions on Thursday afternoons between 5pm and 6pm at Dagenham Park School. The sessions will have a focus on inclusive fun and are open to all young people aged between 11 and 25.\r\nFor more information please contact:\r\nDanielle Smith: Danielle.smith@lbbd.gov.uk 07977 018 832\r\nMarlan Henry: mhenry@premiertrainingnetwork.co.uk 07843 936 170\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=\"width: 40%; padding: 0 5pt 0 0; float: right;\">[fancy_header]3 on 3 Championship[/fancy_header]\r\n[image_frame style=\"framed\" align=\"left\" height=\"150\" width=\"150\"]<img alt=\"536256_587061181395678_2599361266593340468_n\" src=\"http://www.thunderbasketball.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/536256_587061181395678_2599361266593340468_n-e1413958420393-150x150.jpg\" width=\"54\" height=\"54\" />\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /&gt;\"&gt;[/image_frame]\r\n\r\n456 wondered how to create beautiful column layouts on your pages, without any custom coding? If you are using a Press Coders theme, you can use shortcodes to do just that!Shortcodes are small snippets you can co